      <portrait>Carrinas</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Carrinas</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>Commander Marcus Carrinas learned his trade in numerous battles with barbarians and renegade Houses. His tactics lacked finesse, but showed strength and willingness to fight no matter the odds, giving Carrinas the nickname 'the Bull'. The reward for his most recent battle had been a promotion to the rank of Legatus Legionis - and a deep shoulder wound that had never healed properly. Despite his protests, Carrinas was sent to Teron to 'prevent Antidas from doing anything stupid'. Since the Bull had always preferred permanent solutions to problems, he started training new recruits without delay.

"We have received a formal complaint from the merchants' guild. It appears that the local militia is no longer able to protect the town, watching helplessly as raiders, thieves, and other scum attack in broad daylight. Although the rules prevent us from getting involved into the affairs of Noble Houses, I believe that this situation gives us no choice but to get involved. Teron will NOT fall! I can promise you that much!"</npc_text>
