      <npc_text>You start your speech with "We'll lose most men – if not all – in the frontal assault." It gets everyone's attention. "The men on the ground will keep us from getting into the tower while the archers on the battlements will rain arrows from above. We won't stand a chance.

"We need to get to the battlements and attack from above. It will put the archers at a disadvantage and it would take the swordsmen a while to reach us.

"However," you finally get to the most important point. "Someone needs to distract the guards and keep them busy while the rest of us scale the walls."</npc_text>
